OL,3,CAsthma attacks triple as
OL,4,Chospitalisations reach four year high
OL,6,FHis mother, Branwen Niclas, explained
OL,7,Fhow the autumn and winter terms can be
OL,8,Fworrying for parents as the cold and
OL,9,Fwet weather can often aggravate asthma
OL,10,Fsymptoms. It means that son, Huw,
OL,11,Foften has to miss out on activities
OL,12,Fsuch as playing football with his
OL,13,Ffriends.
OL,15,FShe said: "His worst asthma attack in
OL,16,Fschool happened in December 2022. He
OL,17,Fbecame breathless, wheezy, and
OL,18,Fexhausted. Huw didn't return to school
OL,19,Funtil the following week as when his
OL,20,Fasthma worsens all his energy goes
OL,21,Finto taking breaths.
